name: PriusOmega
tweet: What does government mean in a #Bitcoin world?  What it always was supposed to mean. The will of the people. One free from the burden of maintaining accurate price signals, and instead beholden to constituents. W/ A new entry to law:  The separation of money and state.   #Bitcoin

name: PriusOmega
tweet: #Bitcoin is the best money ever invented, that gets better and better at conveying price over time. I realize that right now it is awful, but that is because it doesn't have the adoption or usage rate of the dollar. If it did, prices would be incredibly, incredibly accurate.

name: PriusOmega
tweet: #Bitcoin represents a real crisis for governments. If the markets and the reserve assets of the world chose to denominate in #Bitcoin and not the dollar, the US government loses the means in which it governs. The very core to how it operates.

name: PriusOmega
tweet: #Bitcoin doesn't have any one issuer, or even anybody capable of changing the protocol (doing so is a hard fork and isn't BTC anymore) and it biases issuance towards the enablers of the network, the miners that have to expend resources and create infrastructure. No Government.

name: PriusOmega
tweet: Enter #Bitcoin.  It has a rock solid, perfectly knowable denominator. It is the ideal tool to convey price signals. And it accomplishes this without any human consideration.  For governments of the world, the humans that use fiat as a tool for governance, this is a problem.
